{
  "text": "Weibull factors k and c demonstrate the distribution of the winds for a particular location [CITATION_1] . The following scale is implemented to measure the degree of wind availability: good-f (V) ≥ 0.90; average-0.75 ≤ f (V) < 0.90; and low-f (V) < 0.75.",
  "correct_citation": {
